President Biden and Indian Prime Minister Modi met in the Oval Office to discuss the U.S.-India relationship. Biden expressed his belief that the partnership between the two countries can help solve global challenges. He also shared a personal story about a possible family connection to India. The leaders discussed the shared commitment to ending the COVID pandemic, addressing climate challenges, and ensuring stability in the Indo-Pacific. They emphasized the importance of democratic values and the contributions of Indian Americans in strengthening the United States. Modi praised Biden's leadership and expressed confidence in their ability to work together for the benefit of both countries and the world.